01:50.659 --> 01:53.759
Harley, what are you doing?

01:53.761 --> 01:56.331
- Why did you scream?
- Because you scared me.

01:58.499 --> 02:00.602
Hey, Drooper. Mail's here.

02:02.404 --> 02:03.437
Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!

02:08.476 --> 02:10.710
It's the middle of the night.
Why are you awake?

02:10.711 --> 02:13.479
I'm too excited.
I can't go to sleep.

02:13.481 --> 02:17.049
It's not your birthday yet.

02:17.051 --> 02:19.519
It's past midnight.

02:19.521 --> 02:21.787
Okay.

02:21.789 --> 02:24.793
It is your birthday, but we're
not celebrating it yet.

02:26.594 --> 02:29.831
Come on. Let's go.
Let's get you back to bed.

03:10.004 --> 03:12.172
Mom.

03:12.174 --> 03:15.074
Um, uh, what time is it?

03:15.076 --> 03:18.878
It's past your curfew.
That's what time it is.

03:18.880 --> 03:22.416
Mom, I'm-I'm 19. Why do I
have to be home by midnight?

03:22.418 --> 03:25.484
Because I wanna know that
you're safe before I go to bed.

03:25.486 --> 03:26.919
I worry about you, Austin.

03:26.921 --> 03:29.121
Just,
please don't tell Mitch, okay?

03:29.123 --> 03:31.458
I can't handle
another one of his lectures.

03:31.460 --> 03:33.492
Okay.

03:33.494 --> 03:36.096
Just promise me that you won't
mess with him tomorrow.

03:36.098 --> 03:37.430
I just really want
your brother's birthday

03:37.432 --> 03:38.865
to be perfect.

03:38.867 --> 03:40.803
Yeah, so do I. Me too.

03:42.037 --> 03:43.373
Okay.

03:45.440 --> 03:48.009
- Goodnight.
- Goodnight.

03:58.486 --> 04:00.686
The flu? Really?

04:00.688 --> 04:02.222
You sure?

04:02.224 --> 04:04.691
Wow. Both hands. Okay.

04:04.693 --> 04:08.161
Um, well, I..

04:08.163 --> 04:10.697
Please tell Duncan
I hope he feels better.

04:10.699 --> 04:13.934
Okay, bye.
Duncan has the flu.

04:13.936 --> 04:15.568
He's not gonna be able
to come with us.

04:15.570 --> 04:17.603
Harley's gonna be
so disappointed.

04:17.606 --> 04:18.870
So invite one
of his other friends.

04:18.873 --> 04:20.140
He doesn't have
any other friends.

04:20.142 --> 04:22.111
Duncan's the only one
he plays with.

04:23.245 --> 04:24.614
Really?

04:27.248 --> 04:29.950
There's gotta be someone else
we can invite.

04:29.952 --> 04:31.116
There's not too many kids
his age

04:31.118 --> 04:33.886
that still like that show.

04:33.888 --> 04:35.020
It's because it's stupid, Beth.

04:37.493 --> 04:38.859
It's his favorite show

04:38.861 --> 04:40.826
and I bought tickets
five months ago

04:40.828 --> 04:41.927
so like it or not

04:41.929 --> 04:43.963
we are going to a live taping

04:43.965 --> 04:46.501
of "The Banana Splits."

04:48.637 --> 04:50.006
Great.

04:53.241 --> 04:56.510
♪ Flapping like a pancake
popping like a corn ♪

04:56.512 --> 04:59.513
♪ Fleegle Bingo
Drooper and Snork ♪

04:59.515 --> 05:02.681
♪ Tra la la la-la la la ♪

05:02.683 --> 05:05.217
♪ Tra la la la-la la la ♪♪

05:05.219 --> 05:06.488
Oh!

05:11.960 --> 05:14.059
- 'Hello.'
- Hi.

05:14.061 --> 05:15.595
This is Harley's mom calling.

05:39.287 --> 05:41.054
What are you doing?

05:41.056 --> 05:43.623
Um, looking for my other sock.

05:43.625 --> 05:44.924
Thought, thought
maybe it got mixed up

05:44.926 --> 05:46.258
'with yours, but it didn't.'

05:46.260 --> 05:48.929
So you weren't stealing
money from me?

05:48.931 --> 05:51.864
No. I wasn't, Mitch.

05:51.866 --> 05:53.133
Because you know
if you need money

05:53.135 --> 05:55.701
you can just ask me, right?

05:55.703 --> 05:58.237
Okay.
Can I have, uh, 20 bucks?

05:58.239 --> 06:01.140
No. Not a chance.

06:05.080 --> 06:06.282
Dick.

06:13.087 --> 06:15.020
- Yay!
- Happy birthday, sweetheart.

06:15.022 --> 06:16.791
Happy birthday, buddy.

06:18.092 --> 06:19.662
Happy birthday, Harley.

06:23.164 --> 06:25.765
Oh. A tiny wand.

06:25.767 --> 06:27.937
No, no. Uh, push the button.

06:32.274 --> 06:34.773
Your old one broke,
so I got you a new one.

06:34.775 --> 06:36.275
I love it, Austin.

06:36.277 --> 06:38.979
We have another surprise
for you. We...

06:38.981 --> 06:42.982
Are going
to "The Banana Splits."

06:42.984 --> 06:46.285
Thank you so much, daddy.

06:46.287 --> 06:48.354
- You're the best.
- Harley, we talked about this.

06:48.356 --> 06:50.659
You're too old
to call me daddy, okay?

06:54.962 --> 06:57.696
There's five tickets.
Can Duncan come?

06:57.698 --> 06:59.633
Oh, Duncan is sick, sweetheart

06:59.635 --> 07:01.234
but I called
another one of your friends

07:01.236 --> 07:04.337
and they are so excited to go.

07:04.339 --> 07:06.672
I don't wanna see
"The Banana Splits."

07:06.674 --> 07:09.208
Oh, Zoe, come on. It was nice
enough that they invited you.

07:09.210 --> 07:12.111
- We're not even friends.
- Well, maybe he wants to be.

07:12.113 --> 07:14.347
Mom, he's weird.
He believes in fairies

07:14.349 --> 07:16.982
and thinks he can talk to
animals. Please don't make me.

07:16.984 --> 07:18.785
It's his birthday
and you're going

07:18.787 --> 07:20.886
and that's final.

07:20.888 --> 07:22.321
But that show's for babies.

07:22.323 --> 07:24.657
Oh, and suddenly
you're so mature.

07:24.659 --> 07:26.595
You have bunnies
on your undies.

07:27.828 --> 07:29.895
Go upstairs and get dressed.

07:29.897 --> 07:31.967
They're coming to get you
in ten minutes.

07:40.808 --> 07:42.107
Welcome to Taft Studios.

07:42.109 --> 07:44.277
Hi. Yeah, we're here
to see the, uh...

07:44.279 --> 07:47.112
"The Banana Splits." We're
seeing "The Banana Splits."

07:47.114 --> 07:50.015
- It's my birthday.
- He's a little excited.

07:50.017 --> 07:51.854
Just need your ID.

07:55.356 --> 07:57.924
You're just gonna follow
the main avenue

07:57.926 --> 07:59.893
down to Stage 12.

07:59.895 --> 08:03.229
Hang a right, and then a left,
and then two more rights.

08:03.231 --> 08:06.398
Stage 1 is kind of tucked back
in the corner.

08:06.400 --> 08:09.234
Uh, you know what?
It's all in the map.

08:09.236 --> 08:10.903
Thanks.

08:10.905 --> 08:13.439
I can't believe
you actually get to work here.

08:13.441 --> 08:15.874
Is this the best job
in the world?

08:15.876 --> 08:17.710
Do you know
"The Banana Splits?"

08:17.712 --> 08:19.746
Beth, those wings are staying
in the car.

08:19.748 --> 08:22.381
You know, sometimes at night

08:22.383 --> 08:24.850
when I'm the only one here

08:24.852 --> 08:28.455
I see the Splits riding around
in their little cars

08:28.457 --> 08:31.224
laughin' and singin'.

08:31.226 --> 08:33.696
- Really?
- He's playing with you, Harley.

08:38.967 --> 08:41.500
'Harley, you excited?'

08:41.501 --> 08:43.769
'I really wanna meet Snorky.'

08:43.770 --> 08:45.471
'Zoe, did you ever dream'

08:45.473 --> 08:48.108
'that you'd get to meet
the Banana Splits?'

08:48.110 --> 08:49.408
'No?'

08:49.410 --> 08:52.345
'No, I did not.'

08:52.347 --> 08:55.315
"The Banana Splits" is
me and Austin's favorite show.

08:55.317 --> 08:57.050
'Really?'

08:57.052 --> 08:58.417
'So how long
have you been watching'

08:58.419 --> 09:00.452
' "The Banana Splits?"'

09:00.454 --> 09:02.888
'Uh..'

09:02.890 --> 09:06.058
'I'm-I'm-I'm sure she,
she really loves the show.'

09:06.060 --> 09:08.261
'I hope Snorky
does the Snorky Shuffle.'

09:08.263 --> 09:10.229
'It's so funny.'

09:10.231 --> 09:12.231
'He's totally gonna do it.
He does it every time.'

09:12.233 --> 09:15.033
'Sounds awesome.'

09:15.035 --> 09:17.402
'Oh, map says Stage 1'

09:17.404 --> 09:19.839
'is the oldest sound stage
at Taft Studios.'

09:19.841 --> 09:21.840
'This is going to
be the best birthday ever.'

09:21.842 --> 09:23.779
'I'm never gonna forget it.'

09:32.154 --> 09:34.787
Who's excited to see
"The Banana Splits?"

09:37.292 --> 09:38.825
Hi, I'm Paige.

09:38.827 --> 09:41.226
The audience page.
Paige, the page.

09:41.228 --> 09:43.329
Guess you could say
I was born to do this job.

09:43.331 --> 09:44.497
God, I hope not.

09:44.499 --> 09:46.065
Please have your tickets ready

09:46.067 --> 09:47.466
and I'll get you checked
in lickety-splits.

09:47.468 --> 09:50.069
- Oh!
- That's lame.

09:50.071 --> 09:52.108
I know it's bad.
They make me say it.

09:56.443 --> 09:58.344
Cell phones, please.

09:58.346 --> 10:00.345
'Thank you.
Thank you so much.'

10:00.347 --> 10:02.949
Parker, seriously?
Stop chewing on your hair.

10:02.951 --> 10:04.883
I just paid $70
for that blow up

10:04.885 --> 10:07.019
and straighten up.

10:07.021 --> 10:09.455
What's up, you guys?
Check it out, right?

10:09.457 --> 10:12.224
We're here at the Taft Studios.

10:12.226 --> 10:16.461
The home of "The Banana Splits"
since 1969.

10:16.463 --> 10:20.465
This is hallowed ground,
my friends.

10:20.467 --> 10:22.969
And we're gonna be going live
all day long.

10:22.971 --> 10:24.838
- Behind the scenes.
- Oh, yeah.

10:24.840 --> 10:27.974
Actually, there's no cell phones
allowed inside, so..

10:27.976 --> 10:29.508
Seriously?

10:29.510 --> 10:31.411
I just told all my followers

10:31.413 --> 10:34.013
like all of them,
that I'll be going live.

10:34.015 --> 10:36.248
Well, you can tell your..

10:36.250 --> 10:39.018
...218 followers all about it
after the show.

10:39.020 --> 10:40.887
Yeah.
I'm not giving up my phone.

10:40.889 --> 10:42.892
- Then you can't come in.
- Thadd.

10:44.491 --> 10:46.261
It's fine.

10:49.496 --> 10:51.500
Thanks. Enjoy the show.

11:08.650 --> 11:10.249
Harley!

11:22.264 --> 11:23.428
What the hell
were you thinking?

11:23.430 --> 11:24.898
Mom, did you see that?

11:24.900 --> 11:27.032
I waved at Snorky,
but he didn't wave back.

11:27.034 --> 11:29.167
You have to be more careful
than that.

11:29.169 --> 11:31.104
Mom, Snorky wouldn't hurt me.

11:31.106 --> 11:33.273
He's my favorite.

11:33.275 --> 11:35.675
Zoe,
which one's your favorite?

11:35.677 --> 11:38.677
- The cat.
- There isn't a cat.

11:38.679 --> 11:42.348
Uh, she means the..
Drooper, the lion.

11:42.350 --> 11:44.920
Yeah. That's what I meant.
The lion.

11:46.353 --> 11:49.589
I can't believe
he just ran out like that.

11:49.591 --> 11:51.327
- Mitch.
- Huh?

11:54.663 --> 11:56.195
Hey, I need that. It's work.

11:56.197 --> 11:59.498
Harley was almost hit
by a Banana Buggy.

11:59.500 --> 12:01.700
Jesus, that would have been
an embarrassing way to die.

12:01.702 --> 12:03.436
- Phones, please.
- No, no, no.

12:03.438 --> 12:05.171
I-I need that for work.

12:05.173 --> 12:06.940
Don't worry, they'll be safe
in the production office

12:06.942 --> 12:08.977
till after the show.
Thank you.

12:13.515 --> 12:15.281
Hey, uh, here you go.

12:15.283 --> 12:18.153
You can put your number
in there if you want.

12:21.289 --> 12:24.389
I'm, I'm so sorry.
I don't know why I said that.

12:24.391 --> 12:27.225
I thought it would sound cool,
like-like smooth.

12:27.227 --> 12:28.293
- It didn't.
- Okay.

12:28.295 --> 12:29.494
Just take my phone, please.

12:29.496 --> 12:31.500
I did.. Just hate myself.

12:32.733 --> 12:35.701
- That was painful, bro.
- Hmm. Yeah.

12:35.703 --> 12:37.072
'Yeah.'

13:13.408 --> 13:16.575
How was your drive, boys?

13:16.577 --> 13:19.745
You naughty splits.

13:19.747 --> 13:22.382
You almost hit that little boy.

13:22.384 --> 13:24.383
Someone's reflex subroutine

13:24.385 --> 13:27.387
needs a little tweaking, hm?

13:27.389 --> 13:30.355
We'll start with you, Drooper.
Hmm.

13:30.357 --> 13:33.393
'You boys, get backstage.'

13:33.395 --> 13:34.761
As you know..

13:37.399 --> 13:39.668
The show must go on.

13:49.309 --> 13:51.244
Let's get you updated, eh?

13:51.246 --> 13:53.615
We don't want
any hiccups today, do we?

13:58.419 --> 13:59.587
Ah.

14:10.231 --> 14:11.663
The script says giant hammer.

14:11.665 --> 14:14.302
What I'm holding
is a regular hammer.

14:15.803 --> 14:18.439
No..
Tell Props I'm coming to them.

14:25.813 --> 14:27.613
Where's Drooper?

14:27.615 --> 14:30.182
Does anybody have a 20
on Drooper?

14:30.184 --> 14:32.220
Damn it.
Do I have to do everything?

14:35.255 --> 14:38.191
- Rebecca, you got a minute?
- No. I don't.

14:38.193 --> 14:40.192
'We're about to
start and I'm a Split short.'

14:40.194 --> 14:43.528
Okay, well,
I was gonna do this gently

14:43.530 --> 14:46.099
but since you're in a rush,
I'm canceling the show.

14:46.101 --> 14:47.834
What?

14:47.836 --> 14:50.636
Uh, you probably heard
about my promotion this morning?

14:50.638 --> 14:52.772
No, I didn't.
I'm a little busy, Andy.

14:52.774 --> 14:54.440
Oh, are you?

14:54.442 --> 14:56.742
Well, I'm the vice president
of Programming now

14:56.744 --> 14:58.444
and "The Banana Splits"
doesn't really

14:58.446 --> 15:00.278
represent my vision
for the network.

15:00.280 --> 15:02.581
Are you kidding?
We're still a huge hit.

15:02.583 --> 15:05.585
Yeah, but it's old and stupid.

15:05.587 --> 15:07.887
And I wanna do something cool
and edgy

15:07.889 --> 15:09.888
so today's your last show.

15:09.890 --> 15:12.691
But we have tapings
lined up for weeks.

15:12.693 --> 15:14.429
Not anymore.

15:25.405 --> 15:28.209
Somebody find Karl and tell him
to get Drooper out on stage.

15:40.321 --> 15:42.654
Welcome to "The Banana Splits."

15:45.760 --> 15:47.192
Yay!

15:47.194 --> 15:49.862
Whoo! Hoo-hoo!

15:49.864 --> 15:52.230
Now, I want you all
to check your tickets

15:52.232 --> 15:56.168
'because we've got a little
extra treat for some of you.'

15:56.170 --> 15:58.771
If you've got stars in the back,
then you're in luck.

15:58.773 --> 16:03.242
You get to stay after the show
and meet "The Banana Splits."

16:03.244 --> 16:04.509
And Stevie.

16:04.511 --> 16:06.778
A-and Stevie.
Don't forget Stevie.

16:06.780 --> 16:10.248
- Mom, hurry.
- I know, honey. I'm checking.

16:10.250 --> 16:14.387
Yes! We got stars.
We got stars.

16:14.389 --> 16:16.589
Oh, my God.
Thadd, Thadd!

16:16.591 --> 16:19.495
Baby, we are gonna
meet the Splits.

16:22.529 --> 16:26.135
- We didn't get stars.
- It's okay, honey.

16:38.446 --> 16:42.514
'Taft Studios
presents "The Banana Splits."'

16:45.352 --> 16:46.619
Whoo!

16:46.621 --> 16:48.890
'Starring Fleegle..'

16:51.726 --> 16:53.529
'...Snorky..'

16:56.563 --> 16:58.400
'...Bingo..'

17:04.471 --> 17:05.471
Bingo!

17:05.473 --> 17:07.242
'Drooper.'

17:09.009 --> 17:10.578
'Drooper.'

17:13.281 --> 17:14.445
'Drooper?'

17:14.448 --> 17:17.817
- Where the hell is it?
- It just..

17:17.819 --> 17:19.651
Just go out there and say

17:19.653 --> 17:21.685
Drooper got caught in
Mr. Walterscheid's fence again.

17:21.688 --> 17:24.624
I'll make sure Karl has him
ready for the next scene.

17:24.626 --> 17:26.259
Cue announcer.

17:26.261 --> 17:29.298
'And featuring Stevie.'

17:35.836 --> 17:37.802
Is that man
dressed like a child?

17:37.804 --> 17:41.741
That's Stevie.
Nobody really likes him.

17:41.743 --> 17:43.642
Guys, we have to get Drooper

17:43.644 --> 17:48.013
out of Mr. Walterscheid's fence
again!

17:54.889 --> 17:58.291
'Our first scene
will begin in a few minutes, folks.'

17:58.293 --> 18:01.026
'So sit tight.'

18:01.028 --> 18:03.763
- Where are you going?
- Bathroom, Mitch.

18:03.765 --> 18:06.032
Want a full report
when I get back?

18:06.034 --> 18:09.034
Spoiler alert.
It's a dump.

18:09.036 --> 18:10.838
Don't be long.

18:21.349 --> 18:25.618
Alert Rebecca that
Drooper is functioning at 100%.

18:25.620 --> 18:27.555
I'm sending him to the stage.

18:52.846 --> 18:55.513
'It's Sloppy Time!'

18:55.515 --> 18:58.751
'Give it up
for Ashley and Trevor!'

18:58.753 --> 19:01.920
'Watch out for that slide.'

19:01.922 --> 19:04.790
'Oh, there goes Ashley.'

19:04.792 --> 19:06.458
That should have been you
out there.

19:06.460 --> 19:08.093
I don't wanna get messy.

19:08.095 --> 19:09.895
You wanna get discovered
or not?

19:09.897 --> 19:11.397
Because if you're not
committed to this

19:11.399 --> 19:14.065
you tell me right now.

19:14.067 --> 19:16.804
'And they're
coming up to the balance beam.'

19:19.806 --> 19:22.006
'Watch out for those eyes!'

19:29.583 --> 19:33.619
'Oh, and Trevor's down
for the count.'

19:33.621 --> 19:37.389
'Only one left.
Can she find the blue key?'

19:37.391 --> 19:39.361
I don't know
what's taking Austin so long.

19:40.628 --> 19:43.561
I'll go find him.

19:43.563 --> 19:45.164
No, no, no, no.
You don't have to. It's okay.

19:45.166 --> 19:48.167
No, it's fine. I've gotta check
in the office, anyway, so..

19:48.169 --> 19:49.702
Really?
It's Harley's birthday.

19:49.704 --> 19:51.704
You can't forget about work
for one day?

19:51.706 --> 19:53.438
I'm just gonna check in.

19:53.440 --> 19:55.073
You don't even have
your cell phone.

19:55.075 --> 19:57.879
Then I'll find one
right after I find Austin.

19:59.613 --> 20:00.815
Okay.

20:03.784 --> 20:06.484
'And Ashley's
moving up the ladder.'

20:08.456 --> 20:11.557
Ashley! Ashley! Ashley!

20:11.559 --> 20:13.628
It's time to fly.

20:36.082 --> 20:39.651
She took it down to Hammer Town.

20:39.653 --> 20:42.022
For the love of God,
can somebody find Stevie?

20:44.225 --> 20:47.025
He's in the next scene.

20:48.463 --> 20:49.831
Stevie.

20:51.998 --> 20:54.867
- Are you drunk?
- No.

20:54.869 --> 20:56.668
I'm buzzed.

20:56.670 --> 20:59.571
After this, I'll be drunk.

20:59.573 --> 21:00.773
You want one?

21:00.775 --> 21:02.907
Come on,
they need you on set.

